Fix linker error in debug build (#131)

This shows up on Windows but might also show up elsewhere with `-fvisibility=hidden` (introduced in the 3.9 build). The problem only occurred with debug builds though.

This PR and commit to cpython:

https://github.com/python/cpython/commit/3a4f66707e824ef3a8384827590ebaa6ca463dc0

removed two arguments from _PyBytes_DecodeEscape .

We now call _PyBytes_DecodeEscape with the new signature if the (CPython) minor
version is 9 or greater.

commit.message:
Fix compilation on Python 3.8 (#119)

Two things to do this:
 * Use a version check (instead of a macro definedness check) to determine
   whether to emulate _PyObject_FastCall
 * Use the graminit.h versions of Py_func_type_input and friends
   directly instead of defining them in a compile-ast3.h, since
   Py_func_type_input showed back up in a public header with a
   different value in 3.8 and caused warnings.

importing files.
